## Refactoring Identification

The mutation-based neighbor counting loop (`if (entry) { entry.count++ } else { neighborCounts.set(...) }`) uses mutable state with a conditional. I can simplify this using a plain `Map<string, number>` for counts plus an immutable lookup table for cells, removing the conditional and reducing the object structure complexity.

